text: Boisdinghem is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de- France region in northern France. ==Geography== A small village situated 5 miles (8 km) west of Saint-Omer, on theD206 road. ==Population== ==Sights== * The church of St. Omer, dating from the seventeenth century ==Notable residents== * Alphonse Pinart (1852-1911), explorer, philologist, and ethnographer ==See also== *Communes of the Pas-de-Calais department ==References== * INSEE commune file Category:Communes of Pas-de-Calais
title: Boisdinghem
